dismissalComment.html: is he run out here? the ball was down the leg side, attempted slower delivery, turned towards square leg by Chigumbura, Vermeulen sprints back for the second but Raqibul is quickly onto the ball, he throws it to the bowler who breaks the stumps with Vermeulen short of his crease, Vermeulen had run the first one very slowly, he only stepped on the gas when he was called for the second

commentTextItems.html: Raqibul finishes it with a lofted drive over mid-off for a boundary

commentPostTextItems.html: That was a comprehensive win for Bangladesh, totally outplaying Zimbabwe. On a docile pitch, 207 was just not even runs on the board for Zimbabwe, whose batsmen just couldn't score quickly off Bangladesh's array of spinners.

Junaid and Tamim gave the Bangladesh chase the perfect launchpad, and Ashraful made a near-flawless century to finish the game. Zimbabwe's bowlers need to be more disciplined as well, leaking plenty of extras besides feeding the batsmen with hit-me deliveries.
Sharthak from Bangladesh: "Good win to start the series for Bangladesh. The most impressive part of this win was sensible batting."
Prosper Utseya says his batsmen should have applied themselves better early in the innings so that they could have attacked later in the innings.
Shakib Al Hasan says the boys did a very good job, and is happy with his team's performance.

Mohammad Ashraful is the Man of the Match. "My team-mates have supported me though I didn't do well in the Tests against West Indies," he says. He adds that not being captain has also reduced the burden on him and allowed him to play more freely.
That's it from us here at Cricinfo.  Thanks for all the mails, do join us again for the second ODI on Tuesday

commentTextItems.html: Zimbabwe are helping Bangladesh across the line here, that no-ball means only one more is needed, free-hit time

wanted to finish it off there, but a furious slash is fielded at cover

dismissalText.commentary: Prosper Utseya b Nazmul Hossain 14 (16b 0x4 0x6 20m) SR: 87.5

dismissalComment.html: a yorker does the trick, Utseya misses and offstump is struck again, Zimbabwe are bowled out for 207

dismissalText.commentary: Tamim Iqbal c Coventry b Chigumbura 63 (68b 7x4 0x6 106m) SR: 92.64

dismissalComment.html: the Zimbabwe fans find their voice, they are screaming as Tamim holes out, Tamim was looking to loft it over long-on, mishits it and the ball swirls towards mid-on where Coventry takes a well-judged catch

stories.title: Ashraful ton charges Bangladesh to easy win
stories.subTitle: Zimbabwe v Bangladesh, 1st ODI, Bulawayo
stories.summary: A disciplined bowling performance restricted Zimbabwe to a below-par 207 before Mohammad Ashraful led the chase with a breezy ton to help Bangladesh clinch a facile win in the first ODI in Bulawayo
